Psychical beauty then, like physical, is a gift of nature. It may be developed or disturbed by good or bad training, but it cannot be produced hy art alone.

Further, neither physical nor psychical nor moral beauty exist in nature without alloy. The elements are there, but they have to be discovered by the mind, separated from the dross, and worked into ideal conceptione.
